hopobject.body: What do you do for a living? best viagra copies This year, India will experience only 5 percent growth – the lowest in a decade. Foreign investment has fallen by nearly two-thirds in the past year, and the rupee has plummeted. Although short-term protectionism may appeal to domestic constituencies as the campaign begins for next year's elections in India, history has proven that such policies are inconsistent with a dynamic economy that generates wealth over the long-term. And given the state of its economy, this is hardly the time for India to alienate foreign investors.
